Pietermaritzburg – Five people were injured in Pietermaritzburg on Thursday when parents had to rush their 6-month-old baby to hospital after she was burnt by boiling water, paramedics said. Netcare 911 spokesperson, Chris Botha, said they collided with another vehicle in Mountain Rise. “Paramedics arrived at the scene and found that two people sustained serious injuries while three escaped with minor injuries,” Botha said. The injured patients were transported to hospital.